    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html>\n<head>\n    <title>Floyd-Warshall Algorithm</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            margin: 20px;\n        }\n        #result {\n            font-size: 24px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            margin-top: 20px;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Floyd-Warshall Algorithm</h1>\n    <p>Floyd-Warshall Algorithm is an algorithm for finding the shortest path between all pairs of vertices in a weighted graph. It is a variation of Dijkstra's algorithm.</p>\n    <p>It was first proposed by Robert C. Floyd in 1957 and developed by Stephen Warshall in 1960.</p>\n    <p>Here is a step-by-step textual description of the Floyd-Warshall Algorithm:</p>\n    <ol>\n        <li>Input: A weighted graph represented as an adjacency matrix.</li>\n        <li>Output: The shortest path between all pairs of vertices.</li>\n        <li>Algorithm:</li>\n        <ol>\n            <li>For each vertex i (1 ≤ i ≤ n), find all possible next vertices j (1 ≤ j ≤ n) that can be reached from i.</li>\n            <li>For each pair of vertices i and j, update the shortest distance from i to j if a shorter path is found.</li>\n        </ol>\n    </ol>\n    <p>Here is an example of a weighted graph represented as an adjacency matrix:</p>\n    <table>\n        <tr>\n            <th>Vertex</th>\n            <th>Vertex</th>\n            <th>Vertex</th>\n            <th>Weight</th>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>5</td>\n            <td>6</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n            <td>7</td>\n            <td>8</td>\n        </tr>\n    </table>\n    <p>For the graph above, the shortest distances are calculated as follows:</p>\n    <table>\n        <tr>\n            <th>Vertex</th>\n            <th>Vertex</th>\n            <th>Vertex</th>\n            <th>Weight</th>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>6</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>1</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>5</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n            <td>8</td>\n        </tr>\n    </table>\n    <p>The shortest distances are calculated as follows:</p>\n    <table>\n        <tr>\n            <th>Vertex</th>\n            <th>Vertex</th>\n            <th>Vertex</th>\n            <th>Vertex</th>\n            <th>Weight</th>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n            <td>5</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n            <td>5</td>\n            <td>6</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>4</td>\n            <td>3</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n            <td>5</td>\n            <td>7</td>\n        </tr>\n    </table>\n    <p>The shortest distances between all pairs of vertices are:</p>\n    <table>\n        <tr>\n            <th>Vertex 1</th>\n            <th>Vertex 2</th>\n            <th>Vertex 3</th>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>3</td>\n        </tr>\n    </table>\n    <p>And the shortest distances between all pairs of vertices are:</p>\n    <table>\n        <tr>\n            <th>Vertex 1</th>\n            <th>Vertex 2</th>\n            <th>Vertex 3</th>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>3</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n            <td>1</td>\n            <td>2</td>\n            <td>4</td>\n        </tr>\n    </table>\n    <button id=\"demo-button\">Run Floyd-Warshall Algorithm</button>\n    <script>\n        function floydWarshall(graph) {\n            let n = graph.length;\n            let distances = new Array(n).fill(null).map(() => new Array(n).fill(Infinity));\n            for (let k = 0; k < n; k++) {\n                for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n                    for (let j = 0; j < n; j++) {\n                        distances[i][j] = Math.min(distances[i][j], graph[i][k] + graph[k][j]);\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            return distances;\n        }\n\n        let graph = [\n            [0, 4, Infinity, 7],\n            [Infinity, 0, Infinity, 6],\n            [Infinity, Infinity, 0, 8],\n            [Infinity, Infinity, Infinity, 0]\n        ];\n\n        let distances = floydWarshall(graph);\n\n        let result = \"\";\n        for (let i = 0; i < distances.length; i++) {\n            for (let j = 0; j < distances[i].length; j++) {\n                result += distances[i][j] + \" \";\n            }\n            result += \"\\n\";\n        }\n\n        document.getElementById(\"demo-button\").addEventListener(\"click\", function() {\n            document.getElementById(\"result\").innerHTML = result;\n        });\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
